msgctxt "sn56.47:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 56 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 56 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.47:0.2"
msgid "5. Papātavagga "
msgstr "5. A Cliff "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 47. Paṭhamachiggaḷayugasutta → chiggalasuttaṃ (bj) | chiggaḷa 2 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn56.47:0.3"
msgid "47. Paṭhamachiggaḷayugasutta "
msgstr "47. A Yoke With a Hole (1st) "

# NOTE: BB has “blind”, but the standard meaning of kana is one-eyed, and there seems no reason why not here.
#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.456, sc1
#. VAR: ekacchiggaḷaṃ → ekacchiggalaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn56.47:1.1"
msgid "“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso mahāsamudde ekacchiggaḷaṃ yugaṃ pakkhipeyya. Tatrāpissa kāṇo kacchapo. So vassasatassa vassasatassa accayena sakiṃ sakiṃ ummujjeyya. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, suppose a person was to throw a yoke with a single hole into the ocean. And there was a one-eyed turtle who popped up once every hundred years. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.47:1.2"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn56.47:1.3"
msgid "api nu kho kāṇo kacchapo vassasatassa vassasatassa accayena sakiṃ sakiṃ ummujjanto amusmiṃ ekacchiggaḷe yuge gīvaṃ paveseyyā”ti? "
msgstr "Would that one-eyed turtle, popping up once every hundred years, still poke its neck through the hole in that yoke?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.47:1.4"
msgid "“Yadi nūna, bhante, kadāci karahaci dīghassa addhuno accayenā”ti. "
msgstr "“Only after a very long time, sir, if ever.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
#. VAR: vinipātagatena bālena → vinipātaṃ gatena bālena (si) | vinītagatena bahulena (mr)
msgctxt "sn56.47:2.1"
msgid "“Khippataraṃ kho so, bhikkhave, kāṇo kacchapo vassasatassa vassasatassa accayena sakiṃ sakiṃ ummujjanto amusmiṃ ekacchiggaḷe yuge gīvaṃ paveseyya, na tvevāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sakiṃ vinipātagatena bālena manussattaṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr "“That one-eyed turtle would poke its neck through the hole in that yoke sooner than a fool who has fallen to the underworld would be reborn as a human being, I say. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn56.47:3.1"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "sn56.47:3.2"
msgid "Na hettha, bhikkhave, atthi dhammacariyā, samacariyā, kusalakiriyā, puññakiriyā. "
msgstr "Because there there’s no principled or moral conduct, and no doing what is good and skillful. "

msgctxt "sn56.47:3.3"
msgid "Aññamaññakhādikā ettha, bhikkhave, vattati dubbalakhādikā. "
msgstr "There they just prey on each other, preying on the weak. "

msgctxt "sn56.47:3.4"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "sn56.47:3.5"
msgid "Adiṭṭhattā, bhikkhave, catunnaṃ ariyasaccānaṃ. "
msgstr "It’s because they haven’t seen the four noble truths. "

msgctxt "sn56.47:3.6"
msgid "Katamesaṃ catunnaṃ? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "sn56.47:3.7"
msgid "Dukkhassa ariyasaccassa … pe … dukkhanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāya ariyasaccassa. "
msgstr "The noble truths of suffering, its origin, its cessation, and the path. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn56.47:4.1"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yogo karaṇīyo … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yogo karaṇīyo”ti. "
msgstr "That’s why you should practice meditation …” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn56.47:4.2"
msgid "Sattamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

